Requirements:

    - Have root level access to the local machine; Permission to enable docker daemon
    - Install packages
        a. docker >= v18
        b. gnu-make >= v3.81
    - Specify a 'local_dir' parameter to define which local directory path to browse as 'root'
    - Use 'cd' to navigate to the root of this repository where the "Makefile" is located

Usage:

    * Build and run API locally
        - execute "make run-local"
    
    * Build, run, and test locally
        - execute "make run-local-test"

    * Request all items in a directory
        - execute "curl http://localhost/<:directory-path>/"
    
    * Request file statistics
        - execute "curl http://localhost/<:file-path>"




